The Tabula Iliaca, a small gypsum tablet, with sculptured soenes of the sack of Troy. In the centre we see Aeneas and his family leaving the city under the guidanee of Hermes (Mercury). Aeneas is carrying Anchises (the latter holding the Penates), and leads Asc-anius by the hand, while a female figure (presumably Creusa) follows. Lower down, to our right, the party is embarking.
